HEADWORD: Olecranon
<hw>O*lec"ra*non</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/; <?/ elbow + <grk>krani`on</grk> the head.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The large process at the proximal end of the <partof>ulna</partof>
which projects behind the articulation with the humerus and forms the
bony prominence of the elbow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

